The paper deals with the problem of guarding polygons, which is a classic problem in computational geometry and falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem and presents approximation algorithms, which are topics that fall under the categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of reduction from the Set Cover problem, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
